.TH GET_GCP_TOKEN 1 "February 2026" "v1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
get_gcp_token \- Fetches GCP OIDC ID token for AWS federation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B get_gcp_token
[\fIaudience\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B get_gcp_token
is a utility designed to fetch an OIDC Identity Token from the Google Cloud Metadata Server. 
It is primarily used to facilitate passwordless federation into AWS using IAM Roles for Service Accounts (IRSA) patterns on Compute Engine instances.

The program first checks the \fBAWS_WEB_IDENTITY_TOKEN_FILE\fR environment variable for a target file path. If this variable is not set, it defaults to writing the token to \fB/tmp/gcp_oidc_token\fR.

All status messages (success or error) are logged to standard output (stdout) or standard error (stderr) prefixed with an RFC3339 timestamp and a status indicator (SUCCESS/ERROR).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I audience
The target audience (aud) for the token. Defaults to \fBsts.amazonaws.com\fR.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B AWS_WEB_IDENTITY_TOKEN_FILE
The file path where the fetched token will be written.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /run/user/<UID>/aws_gcp_token
Recommended location for storing the token in memory (tmpfs) to ensure it does not hit physical disk. 
.SH EXAMPLES
.B get_gcp_token
.RS
Fetches a token for sts.amazonaws.com and writes it to the configured path.
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR aws (1),
.BR sts (1)
